The histogram for the energy deposited on the copper block should be a Landau distribution and the one i plotted with my simulation looks like one due to its large tail to the right. 
If I remember correctly it should be a Landau distribution due to the small width of the copper block.

Using the command hloss->Fit("landau"); i can fit the function f(x) = C * L((x - MPV)/Ïƒ) on to the histogramm. Here L(x) is the Landau distribution

